<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Psorothamnus</i> <i>arborescens</i>, <i>Psorothamnus</i> <i>fremontii</i> or <i>Psorothamnus</i> <i>polydenius</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub layer with <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>canescens</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>confertifolia</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>polycarpa</i>, <i>Krascheninnikovia</i> <i>lanata</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i> and <i>Tetradymia</i> spp. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1.5 m; canopy is intermittent to open. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent with seasonal annuals or perennial grasses. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Psorothamnus arborescens </i>and/or <i>P. polydenius</i> > 60% relative cover in the shrub layer (VegCamp 2014b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Psorothamnus arborescens, P. fremontii,</i> and/or <i>P. polydenius</i> > 50% relative cover or co-dominant with <i>Atriplex confertifolia </i>in the shrub layer (Evens et al. 2014).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Intermittent washes, drainage bottoms, partially stabilized sand dunes, upper bajadas with pediment and sheet flow, and low slopes with fine-ashy volcanic tuff. Soils are sandy.  </div>
</div>

        
